		<td><b>Re: Entry Thread - Karate Kick</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">:)<br /><br />The CHR layout is curious. What led you to organize it that way with such irregular gaps?</div><br /><br />For the BG section, I more or less draw the backdrop in the CHR directly, then removed duplicate tiles. Later on as I made more things, I just threw them in the gaps when I needed to.<br /><br />For the sprites, I would draw a single character graphic, then chop it up and shift sections around to save tiles, or remove tiles that were duplicates with other frames. You can actually see a few of the original iOS game's sprites in the lower-right. I marked unused tiles with X graphics so I'd know what is clearly available versus part of a sprite.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


